        <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="0">
            <title>service procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, make sure the transmission is in neutral or park, parking
                        brake is set, and wheels are blocked before doing diagnostic or service procedures on engine or
                        vehicle. Read all safety instructions in the "Safety Information" section of the service manual
                        for this engine.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, make sure the engine has cooled down sufficiently before
                        attempting to remove any components.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>When routing tubing, do not crimp the tubing, run the tubing too close to moving parts, or let
                        the tubing come closer than 2"- 4" of a hot engine surface.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <para>There are several types of breather systems installed on the International VT 275 diesel engines. Use
                one of the following removal procedures depending on the type of breather system currently on the
                engine.
            </para>
            <para>. Open breather system.</para>
            <para>. Impactor system.</para>
            <para>. Impactor system with FAQ 347051 modification.</para>
        </svcproc>
        <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="2">
            <title>Remove - Open Breather System</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the button head wire tie (Figure 1, Item 6) from behind the air cleaner
                    bracket.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the standard wire ties from the ladder clip (Figure 1, Item 3) on the valve cover
                    and the frame rail (Figure 1, Item 7).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0691401" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/j08107.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="208px"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Crankcase Ventilation Hose Assembly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Crankcase breather outlet</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Air inlet duct assembly</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. Wire tie (standard) attached to ladder clip</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. Crankcase ventilation hose assembly</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. Air cleaner assembly</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. Wire tie (button head)</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. Wire tie (standard)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0691402" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/j17017.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="248px"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. Crankcase Ventilation Hose Assembly Mounting</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Elbow</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Crankcase ventilation hose assembly</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. Ladder clip</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. Wire tie</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. M6 hex nut and M6 x 43 x 15 stud bolt</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the M6 hex nut from the upper center breather M6 x 43 x 15 stud bolt (Figure 2,
                    Item 5). Remove and discard ladder clip (Figure 2, Item 3).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the crankcase ventilation hose assembly (Figure 2, Item 2) by turning the elbow
                    (Figure 2, Item 1) 90 degrees and pulling the crankcase ventilation hose assembly elbow out of the
                    crankcase breather outlet. Remove the crankcase ventilation hose assembly from the engine.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the Mass Air Flow (MAF) sensor clamp from the air inlet duct assembly (Figure 1,
                    Item 2). Disconnect boost control tubing. Remove and discard the air inlet duct assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
        <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="2">
            <title>Remove - Impactor System</title>
            <figure id="f0691403" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/j17015.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="352px"
                         scalefitheight="408px"/>
                <caption>Figure 3. Impactor System</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Air inlet duct assembly</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Breather outlet steel tube</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. MAF sensor</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. Air cleaner duct</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. Oil drain hose</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. Impactor mounting bolts</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. Impactor</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. Road draft hose</callout1>
                    <callout1>9. Mounting device</callout1>
                    <callout1>10. Wire ties</callout1>
                    <callout1>11. Mounting device</callout1>
                    <callout1>12. Crankcase ventilation hose assembly</callout1>
                    <callout1>13. Air cleaner</callout1>
                    <callout1>14. Oil drain hose retaining bolt</callout1>
                    <callout1>15. Mounting bracket</callout1>
                    <callout1>16. Oil drain check valve and hoses</callout1>
                    <callout1>17. Breather cover</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>Refer to Figure 3 for Items in parentheses.</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove and discard wire ties (Item 10) that hold the road draft hose to the air cleaner
                    bracket and power steering reservoir bracket.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect air cleaner duct (Item 4) from the air inlet duct assembly (Item 1) by
                    disconnecting the MAF sensor (Item 3) from the air inlet duct assembly (Item 1). Remove air cleaner
                    (Item 13) and air cleaner duct (Item 4 ) as a unit.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove road draft hose (Item 8) from impactor (Item 7) discard the road draft hose.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove oil drain hose (Item 5) from impactor. Remove oil drain hose retaining bolt (Item
                    14) from rear of left cylinder head. Remove the upper portion of the oil drain steel tube, oil drain
                    check valve and hoses (Item 16).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, install the components of the Tube Cap Kit. The kit consists of a
                        hose clamp and tube cap.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the tube cap on the exposed tube end on the side of the oil level gauge tube.
                    Secure cap to tube with the hose clamp.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the crankcase ventilation hose assembly from the breather outlet steel tube (Item
                    2).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two impactor mounting bolts (Item 6) from mounting bracket and lift the mounting
                    bracket, impactor, and crankcase ventilation hose assembly out as an assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect boost control tubing from air inlet duct assembly (Item 1). Remove and
                    discard the air inlet duct assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0691404" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/j06059.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Figure 4. Breather Outlet</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Breather outlet elbow</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Breather upper center bolt</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. Breather upper back bolt</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. Steel tube sealing surface</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent possible engine damage, carefully remove the steel tube from the breather cover
                        without cracking discharge opening in the breather outlet.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove breather cover M6 bolts. Remove breather cover and the steel tube as an assembly
                    from the valve cover.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Carefully remove the breather outlet steel tube (Item 2) and the breather outlet elbow
                    (Figure 4, Item 1) from the breather cover outlet by turning the breather outlet steel tube and
                    breather outlet elbow 90 degrees and pulling the two parts apart. Discard the breather outlet steel
                    tube and breather outlet elbow.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
        <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="0">
            <title>Remove - Impactor System with FAQ 347051 modification</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove and discard wire ties on the road draft hose.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove road draft hose from the steel tube on the valve cover. Discard the road draft
                    hose.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent possible engine damage, carefully remove the steel tube from the breather cover
                        without cracking discharge opening in the breather outlet.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove breather cover M6 bolts. Remove breather and the steel tube as an assembly from
                    the valve cover.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Carefully remove the breather outlet steel tube (Figure 3, Item 2) and breather outlet
                    elbow (Figure 2, Item 1) from the breather outlet by turning the steel tube 90 degrees and pulling
                    the two parts apart. Discard the steel tube.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the air inlet duct assembly (Figure 3, Item 1) from the MAF sensor. Disconnect
                    boost control tubing. Remove and discard the air inlet duct assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
        <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="4">
            <title>Install - Closed Breather System</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the breather cover (if removed) on the valve cover making sure O-rings are in
                    place.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install and tighten M6 fasteners to 11 N&#183;m (96 lbf&#183;in).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install air cleaner (Figure 3, Item 13) and air cleaner duct (Figure 3, Item 4) unit.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0691405" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/j15026.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Figure 5. Tighten Hose Clamp</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the air inlet breather hose duct assembly. Attach to the turbocharger inlet with
                    hose clamp. Tighten hose clamp to 4 to 5 N&#183;m (36 to 48 lbf&#183;in).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Attach air inlet breather hose duct assembly to the MAF sensor (Figure 3, Item 3) with
                    hose clamp. Tighten hose clamp to 4 to 5 N&#183;m (36 to 48 lbf&#183;in).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0691406" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/j15027.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Figure 6. Connect Boost Control Tubing</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Boost control tubing connection on turbocharger pneumatic actuator</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Boost control tubing connection on air inlet breather hose</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect boost control tubing (Figure 6, Item 2).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0691407" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/j15003.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="248px"/>
                <caption>Figure 7. Install Mounting Bolt</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the M6 x 16 bolt through the air inlet breather hose duct assembly mounting
                    bracket to the intake manifold. Tighten the bolt to 13 N&#183;m (115 lbf&#183;in).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0691408" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/j31377.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="248px"/>
                <caption>Figure 8. Crankcase Ventilation Hose Assembly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Crankcase ventilation hose assembly</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Breather cover</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Snap the crankcase ventilation hose assembly elbow into the crankcase breather outlet.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
